        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 6:02PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 602 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Figure Five, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Alma...                           Shibley...
Mulberry...                       Dyer...
Kibler...                         Natural Dam...
Concord...                        Lake Fort Smith...
Mountainburg...                   Chester...
Figure Five...                    Piney...
Lee Creek...                      Uniontown...
Dora...                           Van Buren...
Furry...                          Cedarville...
Rudy...                           Fort Smith...

This includes the following highways,
Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 0 and 24.
Interstate 540 between mile markers 1 and 5.
Interstate 49 between mile markers 22 and 40.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
